<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Inline replaced elements relying on intrinsic dimensions</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#inline-replaced-height" />
        <meta name="flags" content="image" />
        <meta name="assert" content="When height and width both compute to auto and the element has intrinsic height, verify height is the intrinsic height." />
        <style type="text/css">
            div
            {
                border: 5px solid green;
                line-height: 0;
            }
            img
            {
                height: auto;
                width: auto;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the top and bottom edges of the blue box touch the top and bottom inner edges of the green border.</p>
        <div>
            <img alt="Test Image" src="../../../Support/blue100x33.png" />
        </div>
    </body>
</html>